A caracter√≠stica possui herdabilidade de 0,7.

h2 <- 0.7 # heritability

A estima√ß√£o e predi√ß√£o dos efeitos fixos e aleat√≥rios √© dada por:

\(\left[ \begin{array} { l } { \hat { \beta } } \\ { \hat { u } } \end{array} \right] = \left[ \begin{array} { c c } { X ^ { \prime } X } & { X ^ { \prime } Z } \\ { Z ^ { \prime } X } & { Z ^ { \prime } Z + \lambda A ^ { - 1 } } \end{array} \right] ^ { - 1 } \left[ \begin{array} { l } { X ^ { \prime } y } \\ { Z ^ { \prime } y } \end{array} \right]\)

\(\hat{\bf{\theta}} = C^{-1}\bf{n}\)

Definindo as matrizes X e Z:

#Vetor com os fen√≥tipos, matrizes X e Z:

              0,1,0,0,
              0,1,0,0,
              0,1,0,0),nrow=6,byrow=T)

# Facilitando...

MM_solve <- function(fenVec, Xmat, Zmat, Amat, her){
  ## Lambda
  lamb <- (1-her)/her
  
  ## Matriz XX
  XX <- crossprod(Xmat,Xmat)
  
  ## Matriz XZ
  XZ <- t(Xmat) %*% Zmat
  ZX <- t(XZ)
  
  ## Matriz ZZ + lambda*A
  ZZ <-crossprod(Zmat) + lamb*solve(Amat)
  
  #Matriz C
  C <- rbind(cbind(XX, XZ), cbind(ZX,ZZ))
  
  #Vetor n 
  n <- rbind(t(Xmat)%*%fenVec, t(Zmat)%*%fenVec)
  
  #Estimativa do BLUE e dos BLUPs
  theta_hat <- solve(C)%*%n
  
  return(theta_hat)
}

Alterando os valores de herdabilidade

herd <- seq(from = 0.01, to = 0.99, 0.01)

results <- data.frame(rep(NA, 5))
for(i in 1:length(herd))
  results[,i] <- MM_solve(y,X,Z,A,herd[i])

colnames(results) <- herd

for(i in 2:nrow(results))
  results[i,] <- results[i, ] + results[1,]

result_melt <- melt(t(results))
result_melt$Var1 <- as.factor(result_melt$Var1)
result_melt$Var2 <- factor(result_melt$Var2, labels = c("mu", "A", "B", "C", "D"))


ggplot(data=result_melt[which(result_melt$Var2 != "mu"),], aes(x= Var1, y=value, group = Var2, color=Var2)) +
  geom_line() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1)) +
  xlab("Herdabilidade") + ylab("BLUE + BLUP") +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Indiv√≠duos"))
